Name: Description
Poor Children Living in Concentrated Pov: The total poor population under the age of 18 living in extreme-poverty neighborhoods. Extreme-poverty neighborhoods are census tracts with poverty rates of 40 percent or higher. For residents living in concentrated poverty, the burdens of individual poverty are amplified. The obstacles they face may include high crime rates, poor health outcomes, reduced private investments, limited educational and job opportunities, and poor housing conditions.

Name: Source Notes
Poor Children Living in Concentrated Pov: U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates, Table S1701 (2010-2020); retrieved from https://data.census.gov/.

Name: Notes
Poor Children Living in Concentrated Pov: Percents refer to the share of the poor children living in extreme poverty tracts.
